been done around the country.

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:58.370 position:56%
Especially if it's pertinent to what
we do, which is promoting books,

00:00:58.370 --> 00:01:00.900
reading, literacy, and libraries.

00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:03.680
The Center for the Book was
created by Daniel Boorstin

00:01:03.680 --> 00:01:08.390
when he was librarian in
1977, as a way to reach

00:01:08.390 --> 00:01:12.120
out to the general public to
promote books and reading.

00:01:12.120 --> 00:01:16.550
And to encourage the scholarly
study of books and reading.

00:01:16.550 --> 00:01:20.480
Literacy really wasn't a hot
topic when we were created.

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:24.740
It came along, we of course
added literacy promotion to this,

00:01:24.740 --> 00:01:30.180
and as a librarian I've also as
the founding director managed

00:01:30.180 --> 00:01:34.160
to get library promotion
into the equation.

00:01:34.160 --> 00:01:39.130
And we have had a very
fruitful, more than 35 years now

00:01:39.130 --> 00:01:43.600
of a public-private
partnership that promotes books,

00:01:43.600 --> 00:01:46.320
reading, literacy, and libraries.

00:01:46.320 --> 00:01:52.430
We operate largely through a
state center affiliates program.

00:01:52.430 --> 00:01:55.930
Each state now has a
designated Center for the Book.

00:01:55.930 --> 00:02:01.220 position:56%
