00:12:59.650 --> 00:13:01.300
My goal in that book was to find

00:13:01.300 --> 00:13:07.350 position:56%
out historically why people love
these ubiquitous civic institutions.

00:13:07.350 --> 00:13:09.410
And love them they do.

00:13:09.410 --> 00:13:14.160
A 2013 report by the Pew
Research Center's Internet

00:13:14.160 --> 00:13:16.280
and American Life Project noted

00:13:16.280 --> 00:13:19.940
that in the previous decade
every other major institution --

00:13:19.940 --> 00:13:22.840
government, churches,
banks, corporations --

00:13:22.840 --> 00:13:24.880
had fallen in public esteem.

00:13:24.880 --> 00:13:29.230
Except libraries, the
military, and first responders.

00:13:29.230 --> 00:13:32.450
The study also found that
91% of those surveyed

00:13:32.450 --> 00:13:35.460
