And Wayne, from the very beginning
kept hounding me and others

01:01:19.140 --> 01:01:21.540
that I was working with --
which was one of our partners,

01:01:21.540 --> 01:01:26.260
the Romance Society of America
and a couple of others --

01:01:26.260 --> 01:01:31.300
with stories from the 19th Century
about how romance fiction was

01:01:31.300 --> 01:01:38.480
such a popular mainstay of
storytelling and of reading.

01:01:38.480 --> 01:01:42.540
And to this day, Wayne and I
now have a stack of stories

01:01:42.540 --> 01:01:45.990
that we were not able
to use in the symposium.

01:01:45.990 --> 01:01:50.480
But we were able to move
romance fiction as a genre

01:01:50.480 --> 01:01:52.770
into the National Book Festival,

01:01:52.770 --> 01:01:55.720
where it was extremely
popular and it will stay.

01:01:55.720 --> 01:02:00.390
So I look forward to using
some of Wayne's unused stories

01:02:00.390 --> 01:02:04.990
for a good cause for
many years to come.

01:02:04.990 --> 01:02:07.320
We're going to end
with a book signing.

01:02:07.320 --> 01:02:11.330
And there are books available at
the Library of Congress discount.

01:02:11.330 --> 01:02:13.970
Wayne will stick around
to sign them.

01:02:13.970 --> 01:02:16.920
We also have some free giveaways.

01:02:16.920 --> 01:02:19.870
We put together a new
Library of Congress issue

01:02:19.870 --> 01:02:24.420
of our magazine called "LCM" just
in time for the book festival.

01:02:24.420 --> 01:02:26.690
And it's all about
the joy of reading.

01:02:26.690 --> 01:02:31.730
And has a good description of
a lot of activities that are

01:02:31.730 --> 01:02:33.780
in the Center for the Book's ken.

01:02:33.780 --> 01:02:37.970
And I also brought out a stack
to give away of a history

01:02:37.970 --> 01:02:42.020
of the D.C. Public Library
that I write a dozen years ago.

01:02:42.020 --> 01:02:45.030
And I was glad to see some
of those disappearing now

01:02:45.030 --> 01:02:48.610
that Wayne has hit the
D.C. Public Library plug.

01:02:48.610 --> 01:02:51.180
So there will be some of
those that you can take.

01:02:51.180 --> 01:02:52.900
But you're going to
have to buy Wayne's book

01:02:52.900 --> 01:02:55.010
at the discount to
get his signature.

01:02:55.010 --> 01:02:58.400
Let's conclude with another
round of applause for Wayne.

01:02:58.400 --> 01:03:01.850
[Applause]

